      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Dream.Org demonstrates a sophisticated approach to organizational health, evidenced by its <cite id=\"7\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>. Financially, the organization is highly resilient with <cite id=\"7\">4.8 months of working capital</cite> available to sustain operations during economic shifts. Their fundraising model is notably efficient, spending only <cite id=\"7\">$0.07 to raise every $1</cite>, which is significantly better than industry averages. This efficiency allows the leadership, including <cite id=\"8\">CEO Nisha Anand</cite>, to focus on high-level advocacy and <cite id=\"2\">federal funding toolkits</cite> that empower local communities to access green economy resources."
      ],
      "summary": "Dream.Org is a national nonprofit organization dedicated to systemic reform by bridging racial and partisan divides to close prison doors and expand opportunities in the green economy. The organization operates through three primary pillars: <cite id=\"1\">Dream Justice, Dream Green For All, and Dream Tech</cite>. In 2023, the organization managed <cite id=\"8\">$4,091,131 in total revenue</cite>, a significant shift from previous years as it transitioned its financial structure. Despite this revenue change, it maintains a <cite id=\"7\">97.75/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting a high standard of institutional governance. A core component of their current strategy involves <cite id=\"2\">advocacy for federal funding</cite>, specifically targeting <cite id=\"2\">369 instances of federal funding advocacy</cite> to ensure resources reach marginalized communities. Their environmental work focuses on <cite id=\"3\">federal funding awareness</cite>, reaching an estimated <cite id=\"3\">$369 billion in potential resource allocation</cite>. As a <cite id=\"5\">Sadaqah-eligible organization</cite>, Dream.Org provides a platform for donors interested in long-term social equity and environmental justice within the United States.",
